<HEAD><PB REF="339" MS="Y">
To Alexander Pope Esq. $</HEAD>
<OPENER><SALUTE>Sir</SALUTE></OPENER>
<P>I have so great a Trust in your In|dulgence towards me, as to believe you cannot but Patronize this Imitation, so much in your own manner, and whose Birth I may truly say is o$ing to you. In that Confidence, I would not suppre&s;s the Criticisms made upon it by the Reverend Doc|tor, the rather, since he has promised to mend the faults in the next Edition, with the same Goodne&s;s he has practised to Milton. I hope you will believe that while I$pre&s;s my Regard for you, it is only out of Modesty I conceal my Name; since, tho perhaps, I may not profe&s;s myself your admirer so much as some others, I cannot but be, with as much inward Respect, Goodwill, and Zeal as any Man,</P>
<CLOSER><SALUTE>Dear Sir Your most Affectionate and Faithful Servant</SALUTE></CLOSER>
