<LG>
<L>&mdash;Nolim laudarier, inquit,</L>
<L>$ic me, mirator <HI>CUNNI CUPIENNIUS ALBI</HI> <NOTE N="*" PLACE="foot">$unni $upiennius Albi, Heary Shrine. Here the Imitator grierously errs, Cunnus Albus by no means signifying a white or grey thing, but a Thing under a white or grey Garment, which thing may be either black, $brown, red, or parti-colour'd. <BIBL>Bent.</BIBL></NOTE></L>
