</DIV2>
</DIV1>
<DIV1>
<PB REF="346" MS="Y">
<LG>
<L>Utque illis multo corrupta dolore voluptas,</L>
<L>Atque haec rara, cadat dura inter saepe pericla.</L>
<L>Hic se praecipitem tecto dedit: ille flagellis</L>
<L>Admortem caesus: fugiens hic decidet acrem</L>
<L>Pracdonum in turbam: dedit hic pro corpore nummos:</L>
<L>Hunc permuxerunt calones; quin eliam illud</L>
<L>Accidit, ut<NOTE N="*" PLACE="foot">Testis Caudamque Salacem Demeterent ferro (for so I say, and not Demeteret ferrum, Bleeds in Person. Silly! was he let Blood by a Surgeon? how short is this of the Amputation of the Testes and Cauda salaae? What Ignorance also of Ancient Learning, appears in his shallow Translation of Perminxerunt, totally mi&s;sing the Mark, and not entering into the deep meaning of the Author.</NOTE> cuidam <HI>TESTIS, CAUDAMQUE SALACE$</HI></L>
<L>Demeterent ferro, jure omnes. Galba negabat.</L>
</LG>
<LG>
<L>Tutior at quanto mer$est in cla&s;se secunda!</L>
<L>Libertinarum dico: Sallustius in qua</L>
<L>Nenminus insanit, quam qui moechatur. at$iosi,</L>
<L>Qua res, qua ratio suaderet, quaque modeste</L>
<L>Munifico e&s;se licet, vellet bonus atque benignus</L>
<L>E&s;se; daret quantum satis e&s;set, ne$ sibi damno</L>
<L>Dedecorique foret. verum hoc se amplectitur uno,</L>
</LG>
</DIV1>
<DIV1>
<DIV2>
<PB REF="347" MS="Y">
<LG>
<L>Attend, while I their Miseries explain,</L>
<L>And pity men of Pleasure still in Pain!</L>
<L>Survey the Pangs they bear, the Risques the$run,</L>
<L>Where the most lucky are but last undone.</L>
<L>See wretched Monsieur flies to save his Throat,</L>
<L>And quits his Mistre&s;s, Money, Ring, and Note!</L>
<L>K&mdash;of his Footman's borrow'd $wory stript,</L>
<L>By worthier Footmen pist upon and whipt!</L>
<L>Plunder'd by Thieves, or Sawyers which is worse,</L>
<L>One bleeds in Person, and one bleeds in Purse;</L>
<L>This meets a Blanket, and that meets a budgel&mdash;</L>
<L>And all applaud the Justice&mdash;All, but<NOTE N="*" PLACE="foot">A Gentleman as celebrated for his Gallantries at his $oliticks; an Entertaining History of which may be published, without the least Scandal on the $adies. <BIBL>E. Curl.</BIBL></NOTE> Budgel.</L>
</LG>
<LG>
<L>How much more safe, dear Countrymen! his State,</L>
<L>Who trades in Trigates of the second Rate?</L>
<L>And yet some Care of S&mdash;st should be had,</L>
<L>Nothing so mean for which he can't run mad;</L>
<L>His confirms him but a Slave the more,</L>
