</LG>
<LG>
<L>Hath not indulgent Nature spread a Feast,</L>
<L><NOTE N="&idagger;" PLACE="foot">The original Manuscript has it,
<Q><L>&mdash;Spread a Feast</L>
<L>Of&mdash;enough for Man, enough for Beast:</L></Q>
but we prefer the present, as the purer Diction.</NOTE> And giv'n enough for Man, enough for Beast?</L>
